mint-themes-gtk3 (3.18+1) sarah; urgency=medium

  [ JosephMcc ]
  * srolled-window: Add support for over/undershoot and add theming for new style scrollbars. Could still use some tweaking but makes it useable.
  * menus: Fix the appearance of menu separators
  * Improve theming of list-row and add theming for sidebars
  * completely rework border images for most widgets. Gtk now support much more complex css in some cases which allows ditching a lot of the image based borders. Doing so simplifies adding support for a lot of newer .vertical linked widgets
  * Rework header bar styling so applications that move the header bar into the primary toolbar position, such as many ubuntu patched apps, get the proper theming
  * add a missing hilight on primary toolbar insensitive buttons

 -- Clement Lefebvre <root@linuxmint.com>  Mon, 15 Feb 2016 10:00:14 +0000

